  "description": "<p>· Follow all traffic laws</p><p>· Drive defensively to ensure safety</p><p>· Ensure that car maintenance is taken care of</p><p>· Keep accurate count of gas usage, miles, and other data</p><p>· Valid driver’s license.</p><p>· Clean driving record for at least one year</p><p>· Good communication and interpersonal skills</p><p>· Familiarity with the local area</p><p>· Operate company vehicles to make pickups and deliveries</p><p>· Help with loading and unloading vehicles.</p><p>· Open to working nights and weekends</p><p>· Great time management skills</p><p>· Great customer attitude and attentiveness</p><p>· Represent the company positively and professionally in interactions with customers and the general public</p><p>· Gain a thorough understanding of the local area and the most efficient routes</p><p>Availability:Able to work on weekends, public holidays, and night shifts.</p><p>We thank you for your interest and we regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. All resumes received will be used for recruitment purposes only.</p><p>EA License ID: 18C9520</p><p>EA Registration ID: R1765753</p>",
